/** --------------------------------------------------
             Carry normalization — available algorithms

  CARRY_ALG_SINGLE_TILE — 1 block per candidate, MR_CARRY_TILE threads.
    All tiles of a candidate are processed by a single block with
    shared-memory carry between tiles. Lower GPU occupancy but simple.

  CARRY_ALG_MULTI_TILE  — 2 separate phases:
    Phase 1 (intra): n_tiles × n_batch blocks in parallel, each one
      normalizes MR_CARRY_TILE elements with an output carry in d_tile_carry.
    Phase 2 (inter): 1 thread per candidate, propagates carries between tiles
      sequentially. Better occupancy in the intra phase.

  CARRY_ALG_SEQUENTIAL  — 1 thread per candidate, pure sequential loop
    over all elements. Minimal shared memory, maximal serialization.
    Useful as a baseline or when other algorithms have race conditions.

------------------------------------------------------*/

#define CARRY_NORM_ALG @CARRY_NORM_ALG@

